item.title: About Me
item.dc:creator: murphy5711
item.content:encoded: Hi, I'm Graham and i am a third year Creative Digital Media student in the Institute of Technology Blanchardstown. I am a highly motivated and ambitious individual, currently building on my knowledge and skills . i have excellent attention to detail, having this lets my come up with the best solution in all of my modules. i have a diversified skill set covering Videography, Audio/Video editing, Graphic Design and Photography. Im able to use own initiative and work as part of team under pressure to meet challenging deadlines and objectives. I have excellent inter-personal and digital communication skills, with a great determination to succeed in everything i do. item.title: Video
item.dc:creator: murphy5711
item.content:encoded:
Oblivious

This is a short film I made for my second year group project to raise aware of the homelessness crisis in Ireland My role in this project was to film and edit along with filling in as an extra in the film. This film was made my myself and my three classmates Ross Kelly, Zoe Gilligan and Kaylee Kinsella.

The Recession in Ireland

The Recession in Ireland was made my me and a classmate as part of an assignment in second year . The documentary is about what the recession was about how it affected Ireland. This short documentary contains two interviews of people affected by the rescission and you can hear a short description of their stories. The equipment used in this film was a Canon 70D DSLR camera and a full sound kit with a boom and a H6 recorder. It was also edited on Premier Pro.

Short Music video

This is a short music I made in first year as part of a one day lab for my module Digital Video. It was filmed on an phone 5 and edited using Premiere Pro
